Hi, Melissa.

As melissa  wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/24/2004 at 11:55:31 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>is it possible to convert ml to cm or mm? if so can i have the 
>formula? 
>
>[Difficulty]
>to convert liters to centimeters
>
>[Thoughts]
>i don't have any.

Liters are a measure of volume, while meters measure length; you 
can't convert two different types of quantity. However, a milliliter 
is defined as a CUBIC centimeter, so a liter is 1000 cm^3.

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


